quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  51,1,"By the winds that scatters [dust]"
  51,2,and by the heavily-laden clouds with water
  51,3,and by the ships that sail with ease
  51,4,"and by the angels who distribute [blessings] by His command"
  51,5,"Indeed, what you are promised is true"
  51,6,and the Judgment will surely come to pass
  51,7,By the heaven with its pathways
  51,8,"Indeed, you [Makkans] have conflicting views [about the truth]"
  51,9,He who is diverted from it is destined to be diverted
  51,10,Doomed are those who base their beliefs on conjecture
  51,11,those who are steeped in ignorance heedlessly
  51,12,"They ask [mockingly], “When is the Day of Judgment?”"
  51,13,It is the Day when they will be punished by the Fire
  51,14,"[It will be said], “Taste your punishment! This is what you were seeking to hasten.”"
  51,15,"Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and springs"
  51,16,"receiving what their Lord will give them, for they were indeed doers of good beforehand"
  51,17,They used to sleep but little at night
  51,18,and before dawn they would seek forgiveness
  51,19,"and in their wealth, there was a share for the beggar and the destitute"
  51,20,On earth there are signs for those who are certain in faith
  51,21,and also in your own selves. Do you not see
  51,22,And in the heaven is your provision and all that you are promised
  51,23,"By the Lord of the heaven and earth, this [resurrection] is certainly as true as the fact that you can speak"